narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's Harold Bloom. He's hilarious and amazing. Good luck getting in, but if you do, it's worth it. Who knows how long he'll be around. I love you Professor Bloom!

An incredible seminar with an incredible man, scholar, and mind. This isn't a seminar where the student should expect riveting discussion; this is more of an opportunity to listen to a master talk passionately about his life's work. It was an honor to be in Professor Bloom's seminar.
Definitely take this class. A wonderful new way to understand Shakespearian character through comparisons of four of the greatest.
